race.description: Burson Auto Parts Classic Car Cup Handicap (Bm58)
race.comment: MOSGIEL DAISY (2) consistent mare at her peak now and ready for the mile. Won with plenty in hand when coming from last on the turn to salute over 1450m at Kempsey. Has a decent record on her home track and winning rider retains the ride. Can race a little closer and gets the right tempo. FOX REIGN (4) last two runs had merit and placed at the mile. Shouldered the 58.5kg when a narrow second over 1450m at Kempsey. Gets the right set-up again and expected to go close. GOLDEN HONOUR (1) saves his best for is home track and looking for the mile third-up. Back in grade and not to be overlooked. WARRANT (3) will be fitter for recent racing and could show more.
